<head>
  {% css 'test' %}
  {% js 'somefile' %}
  {% load_compilers %}
</head>
<body>
  <p>
    If <code>DEBUG_LESS</code> is set to <code>True</code> in the <code>settings.py</code>
    file, the styles will be loaded directly from the <code>less/test.less</code> file in the
    assets directory. Otherwise, it will be loaded from the <code>css/test.css</code> file.
  </p>

  <p>
    If <code>DEBUG_LESS</code> is enabled, a JavaScript file may be imported to handle
    client-side LESS compilation. This is configured using the <code>CLIENT_LESS_COMPILER</code>
    setting. This is rendered by adding the <code>compile_less</code> tag.
  </p>

  <p>The Jinja tags for this page look like this:</p>

<pre>
{&#37; css 'test' %}
{&#37; compile_less %}
</pre>

  <p>
    If this text is not styled, the LESS file may not be compiled. If you are using Gulp,
    ensure that Gulp is installed, and that it has been compiled using <code>gulp compile</code>
    or <code>gulp watch</code>.
  </p>
</body>
